&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;                   Senior Fellow in Young Adult Hips&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term for 12 month: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;August 2021 – August 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(2 Post available) &lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital is seeking to recruit two Senior Fellow in Young Adult Hip Surgery to increase capacity and improve delivery of high quality Reconstructive and Arthroscopic Surgery to patients referred from General Practitioners, other secondary and tertiary care providers.  At the Royal Orthopaedic Hospital, the Fellow would join a surgical team of two orthopaedic surgeons who work exclusively in Young Adult Hip and a number of other colleagues to ensure maximal efficiency within the department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The department undertakes a comprehensive range of surgical procedures with particular expertise in hip preservation surgery. It is intended that the appointee will be able to gain experience in Hip Arthroscopy and the Arthroscopic management of femoro-acetabular impingement. It is also anticipated that they will gain experience of pelvic and femoral osteotomies for the management of the sequelae of hip dysplasia, SCFU and Perthes in Young Adults. They will also gain experience in complex primary hip arthroplasty.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The individual appointed to the post will have competed orthopaedic training and be on the Specialist Register for Trauma and Orthopaedics and may have already completed or be undertaking a training Fellowship in Young Adult Hip Surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There may be a requirement to participate in the Trust On-Call rota&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications must be made via NHS Jobs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interested applicants are invited to visit on an informal basis by arrangement with:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mr &lt;/span&gt;Mr C McBryde&lt;span&gt;: - &lt;/span&gt;Consultant in Young Adult Hip Surgery: &lt;span&gt;Tel: 0121 685 4298&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
